e of measuring cup, simmer <b>5-10 min\/98°C\/\/speed <b> until fish is cooked."},{"content":"Fluff couscous with a fork. Remove fish pieces with a slotted spoon and arrange over couscous. Pour over a little more sauce. Scatter with almonds and parsley then serve, with remaining sauce on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This dish is a celebration of the diversity of Sicilian cuisine, a region that has been influenced over time by the different cultures that settled there. Couscous is a traditional Moroccan grain that was brought to Italy in the 12th century. Trapani is a city in western Sicily with a traditional way of preparing fish couscous featuring almonds, which grow all over the Sicilian countryside. Together with fragrant cinnamon, they provide the perfect flavour backdrop to the tender, flaked fish."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","4 portions"]}